cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of a data mining methodology using Support Vector Machine algorithm for smart building ventilation subsystem control. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the challenges of effective handling of rich data streams in building monitoring and control through networks of interconnected devices. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper presents a case study on four air handling units of a modern campus building for preliminary decision support for facility managers. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the application of black-box modelling achieved using data mining techniques for smart building ventilation subsystem control. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper also discusses the challenges related to online operation within a commercial Building Management System, indicating a software engineering aspect.
